This is a convenience repo to showcase the gr-webspectrum module as the datasource for a web-based waterfall. When built, a Docker image is produced that contains GNURadio, the gr-webspectrum module, a Redis backend and Uvicorn ASGI webserver.
This repo links to gr-webspectrum as a submodule. (https://github.com/muaddib1984/gr-webspectrum). More details can be found there.
Docker Container Basic Contents:
-Alpine Linux
-GNURadio 3.10.7
-gr-webspectrum
-redis
-uvicorn

to build, run:
docker build -t webspectrum .

to run:
docker run -p 8000:8000 webspectrum

navigate to 0.0.0.0:8000 to see the keyboard shortcuts, click "start viewing spectrum" to see the spectral display
-or-
navigate to 0.0.0.0:8000/spectral to see the spectrum directly



